            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "I tried to run a web search as you asked, but the search tool returned an error. I can retry — would you like me to try again now?\n\nIf by “this place” you mean Centralia, Pennsylvania (your estimated location), here’s a concise description of what’s special about it:\n\n- Long‑running underground coal‑mine fire: A coal seam fire that began in 1962 has burned beneath the town for decades, making Centralia famous (and infamous).  \n- Ghost‑town landscape: Because of the fire, most residents were relocated over the years and buildings were demolished; the town is mostly abandoned and known for empty streets and few remaining homes.  \n- Visible ground effects: Cracks, steam or smoke venting from the ground, occasional sinkholes and subsidence make the area eerie and geologically unstable.  \n- Road closure and lost ZIP code: Major roads were closed or rerouted near Centralia and the town’s ZIP code was officially retired (actions taken over years as the fire and safety concerns progressed).  \n- Cultural influence: Centralia’s atmosphere inspired fictional works (most famously cited as an influence on the setting for the Silent Hill series) and it attracts interest from photographers, urban explorers, and journalists.\n\nIf you meant a different place or want up‑to‑date specifics (current population, government status, recent news, photos, or sources), tell me which place and I’ll retry the web search and include citations.",
